#Text=Nishitokyo
#Text=Nishitokyo ( 西東京市 Nishitōkyō-shi ) is a city in Tokyo prefecture .
#Text=Understand
#Text=Nishitokyo is located in western Tokyo , about 30 minutes by train from Shinjuku .
#Text=Like much of western Tokyo , it 's largely residential , with businesses concentrated around the train stations .
#Text=The area has a lot of small parks and trees , in contrast with central Tokyo , which has skyscrapers and a lot more concrete .
#Text=Get in
#Text=The only train line running through the city is the Seibu Shinjuku Line ( 西武新宿線 ) , which ends in Shinjuku to the east and Hon-Kawagoe to the west .
#Text=See
#Text=Skytower West Tokyo ( スカイタワー西東京 ) ( 20 minutes ' walk WNW from Tanashi Station . ) .
#Text=This tall tower is perhaps the only iconic landmark in Nishitokyo .
#Text=At night , it lights in varying colors .
#Text=Do
#Text=DyDo Drinco Ice Arena ( ダイドードリンコアイスアリーナ ) , Higashi Fushimi 3-1-25 ( Just SE of Higashi Fushimi Station . ) , ☏ +81 42-467-7171 .

column3: ダイドードリンコアイスアリーナ

column1: #Text=This ice rink has ice hockey and public skating .
#Text=On weekends , there are very limited public skating hours , so calling in advance to check on open skating times is recommended .
#Text=Open skating ¥ 1200 admission , ¥ 500 skate rental .
#Text=Tamako Jitenshado ( 多摩湖自転車道 ) ( The southern terminus is on the main thoroughfare Itsukaichikaido and just across the street from Gusto in northern Musashino .
#Text=) .
#Text=This twelve kilometer bike and pedestrian path begins along the southern edge of Nishitokyo , runs fairly straight NW , and terminates far to the NW at two reservoirs .
#Text=It makes for a nice walk or leisurely bike ride of any desirable length .
#Text=Buy
#Text=The best shopping in Nishitokyo is found around the north side of Tanashi Station , where there are several department stores and many other shops .
#Text=Jupiter Coffee ( ジュピターコーヒー ) , Tanashicho 2-1-1 ( In the basement of the Seibu department store just north of Tanashi Station . ) , ☏ +81 42-460-2661 .
#Text=This shop has best selection of foreign food in Nishitokyo .
#Text=Eat
#Text=Restaurants are found in concentration near Tanashi Station .
#Text=Abiskar ( アビスカ ) , Prince Plaza 109 , Minamimachi 4-4-2 ( Several hundred meters east of Tanashi Station 's south exit , on the right . ) , ☏ +81 4-2469-7880 .
#Text=11AM-3PM , 5PM-11:30PM .
#Text=A small Nepalese-Indian restaurant , great for budget travelers .
#Text=¥ 700 sets .
#Text=Dropkick ( ドロップキック ) , Tanashicho 3-11-9 , ☏ +81 42-467-6337 .
#Text=This restaurant specializes in okonomiyaki and has a well-stocked bar . ¥ 600 - 1200 per plate .
#Text=Mae Sre Ruan ( メースィールアン ) , Minamimachi 5-5-1 ( 50m south of the south entrance to Tanashi Station . ) , ☏ +81 424-67-3280 .
#Text=This Thai restaurant serves tasty Thai fare . ¥ 700 - 1400 per plate .
#Text=RAJ ( らじ ) , Minamicho 4-1-15 ( 70m south of the south entrance to Tanashi Station .
#Text=Next to Seven-Eleven ) , ☏ +81 42-463-5530 .
#Text=Daily 11AM-3PM , 5PM-11PM .
#Text=An Indian restaurant that makes for a good late evening stop . ¥ 500 - 1000.
#Text=TEXAS ( テキサス ) , Tanashi-cho 3-3-8 ( From the north exit of Tanashi Station , go two traffic lights north .
#Text=The restaurant is on the right about 30 meters before the second light . ) , ☏ +81 42-466-2898 .
#Text=M - F 11:30AM-3:30PM , 5:30-midnight ; Sa - Su 11:30AM-midnight .
#Text=This is a western-style steak house serving hamburgers , steaks , and a number of desserts . ¥ 1000 - 3000.
#Text=Ichikawa ( いち川 ) , Minamicho 4-4-2 ( From the south exit of Tanashi Station , go east parallel to the tracks for around 200m .
#Text=The restaurant is in a covered row of shops just south of the street . ) , ☏ +81 42-468-7559 .
#Text=M - F 11:30AM-1:30PM , 5PM-9PM ; Sa 11:30AM-1:30PM , 4:30PM-9PM .
#Text=A small and tasty and clean tempura restaurant . ¥ 700 - 1500.
#Text=Yamatoken ( 大和軒 ) , Mukodaicho 1-20-11 ( 20 minutes walk SWS from Tanashi Station .
#Text=Located opposite Mukodai Park . ) , ☏ +81 42-461-3323 .
#Text=A mom-and-pop Japanese diner .
#Text=Serving size is large .
#Text=Drink
#Text=Karaoke Mokomoko ( カラオケモコモコ ) , Tanashicho 3-9-14 ( 2 blocks NE of Tanashi Station . ) , ☏ +81 42-463-5733 .
#Text=This is a clean karaoke parlor with an extensive drink list .
#Text=The song selection is quite extensive .
#Text=SHOUN , Sky Building 5F , Tanashicho 2-2-3 ( From the north exit of Tanashi Station , walk north to McDonald 's .
#Text=The Sky Building is NE diagonally across the street .
#Text=Take the elevator to the fifth floor . ) , ☏ +81 42-446-7000 .
#Text=M , W , Th , Su 6PM-3AM ; F - Sa 6PM-5AM .
#Text=A bar with standard drinks , lots of whiskey , and tasty appetizers .
#Text=Drinks ¥ 300 - 800.
#Text=Half Yard ( ハーフヤード ) , Tanashi Daini Marble Building B1 , Tanashi-cho 4-28-14 ( From the north exit of Tanashi Station , go NW 100m .
#Text=Look for a sign and stairwell on the west side of the street . ) , ☏ +81 50-5789-1742 .
#Text=5PM-2AM .
#Text=This beer hall has many international beers in the bottle and a few on tap .
#Text=The food is well-prepared pub fare .
#Text=The place is clean , and there are several big-screen TVs showing sports .
#Text=cover ¥ 100 , drinks ¥ 600 - 1,200.
#Text=Sleep
#Text=If you have no specific reason to stay in this area , Shinjuku is thirty minutes by train , centrally located , and has a large selection hotels .
#Text=Shirakawa Ryokan ( 白河旅館 ) , Tanashicho 4-6-8 ( From the north exit of Tanashi Station , go west along the train tracks for 300m . ) , ☏ +81 42-461-4438 .
#Text=This is a small and clean ryokan .
#Text=The staff are friendly and helpful , but they only speak Japanese .
#Text=Reservations by telephone , also only in Japanese .
#Text=Room and breakfast ¥ 6000 per person .
#Text=Connect
#Text=Nishitokyo City Hall ( 西東京市役所 ) , 5-6-13 Minamicho ( 300m SW of Tanashi Station . ) , ☏ +81 42-464-1311 .
#Text=City Hall has essential for long-term residents of the city .
#Text=Important information is available in Japanese and ( on paper ) in English .
#Text=Go next
#Text=To the south is Musashino , home of the popular shopping area Kichijoji .
